solar saros 145 wikipedia animated path of entire saros total solar eclipse of august 11 1999 from france member 21 of saros series 145 total solar eclipse of august 21 2017 from simpsonville south carolina member 22 of saros series 145 solar saros 145 is an eclipse cycle with 77 solar eclipses repeating every 18 years 11 days 8 hours it is currently a young cycle producing total eclipses less than 3 minutes in length the longest duration eclipse in the cycle will be member 50 at 7 minutes and 12 seconds in length after which the durations of eclipses will decrease until the end of the cycle in its central phase it will produce mainly total eclipses 41 of 43 central eclipses events edit 